---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../../styles/guided-tool.css';
---

<Base title="Inner Compass - May">

  <section class="tool-hero">
    <span class="tool-label">tool 04</span>
    <h1>Inner Compass</h1>
    <p class="tool-intro">
      Your body knows things your head hasn't understood yet. This tool helps you use
      the body as a guide - to separate healthy fear from real misalignment.
    </p>
    <p class="tool-origin">Based on Martha Beck - Finding Your Own North Star</p>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="guided-experience" id="experience">

    <!-- Resume prompt -->
    <div class="resume-prompt">
      <p></p>
      <div class="resume-actions">
        <button class="btn-primary btn-resume">continue</button>
        <button class="btn-secondary btn-restart">start over</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Unified fractal visualization -->
    <div class="fractal-viz" id="fractal-viz"></div>

    <!-- Transition screen -->
    <div class="transition-screen">
      <div class="transition-dots"><span>.</span><span>.</span><span>.</span></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Completion breath -->
    <div class="completion-breath">
      <div class="breath-text"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 0: Intro -->
    <div class="step active" data-step="0">
      <div class="step-content">
        <p class="step-context">
          Martha Beck calls your "essential self" the part of you that knows before you think.
          It's what tightens your stomach when something is wrong and expands your chest
          when something is right - even when logic says otherwise.
        </p>
        <p class="step-context">
          Here you'll listen to that signal. It's not mysticism - it's body awareness.
        </p>
        <button class="btn-primary step-next">begin <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 1 -->
    <div class="step" data-step="1">
      <div class="step-header">
        <span class="step-number">1 de 6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="ai-insight">
          <span class="ai-insight-marker">✦ reflection</span>
          <p class="ai-insight-text"></p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-encouragement"></div>
        <h2>What's unsettling you?</h2>
        <p class="step-guide">
          Describe the situation you're living - a decision, a relationship, a job,
          a phase of life. Don't try to solve it. Just put on the table what's there.
        </p>
        <textarea id="q1" placeholder="What's unsettling me right now is..." rows="5"></textarea>
        <div class="step-nav">
          <button class="btn-secondary step-prev"><span class="arrow">←</span> back</button>
          <button class="btn-primary step-next">next <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2 -->
    <div class="step" data-step="2">
      <div class="step-header">
        <span class="step-number">2 de 6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="ai-insight">
          <span class="ai-insight-marker">✦ reflection</span>
          <p class="ai-insight-text"></p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-encouragement"></div>
        <h2>What does your head say?</h2>
        <p class="step-guide">
          Write down the rational arguments. What "makes sense"? What would others say?
          What would the "responsible" version of you decide? This is the voice of the social self.
        </p>
        <textarea id="q2" placeholder="Rationally, I should..." rows="5"></textarea>
        <div class="step-nav">
          <button class="btn-secondary step-prev"><span class="arrow">←</span> back</button>
          <button class="btn-primary step-next">next <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3 -->
    <div class="step" data-step="3">
      <div class="step-header">
        <span class="step-number">3 de 6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="ai-insight">
          <span class="ai-insight-marker">✦ reflection</span>
          <p class="ai-insight-text"></p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-encouragement"></div>
        <h2>What does your body say?</h2>
        <p class="step-guide">
          Stop. Take three deep breaths. Think about the situation and pay attention:
          where in your body do you feel something? Chest, stomach, throat, shoulders?
          Is it contraction or expansion? Heaviness or lightness? Describe without interpreting.
        </p>
        <textarea id="q3" placeholder="In my body, I feel..." rows="5"></textarea>
        <div class="step-nav">
          <button class="btn-secondary step-prev"><span class="arrow">←</span> back</button>
          <button class="btn-primary step-next">next <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 4 -->
    <div class="step" data-step="4">
      <div class="step-header">
        <span class="step-number">4 de 6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="ai-insight">
          <span class="ai-insight-marker">✦ reflection</span>
          <p class="ai-insight-text"></p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-encouragement"></div>
        <h2>Fear or misalignment?</h2>
        <p class="step-guide">
          Not all discomfort is a danger signal. Sometimes it's fear of growth - and the path forward is to advance.
          Sometimes the body is saying "this isn't for me" - and the path is to step back.
          Looking at what you wrote: does the discomfort feel like healthy fear (of something that matters)
          or real misalignment (of something that isn't yours)?
        </p>
        <textarea id="q4" placeholder="I think this discomfort is..." rows="5"></textarea>
        <div class="step-nav">
          <button class="btn-secondary step-prev"><span class="arrow">←</span> back</button>
          <button class="btn-primary step-next">next <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 5 -->
    <div class="step" data-step="5">
      <div class="step-header">
        <span class="step-number">5 de 6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="ai-insight">
          <span class="ai-insight-marker">✦ reflection</span>
          <p class="ai-insight-text"></p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-encouragement"></div>
        <h2>What does your essential self want?</h2>
        <p class="step-guide">
          If you removed all expectations - family, career, status, what you "should" do —
          what would be left? What would you do if you only had to answer to yourself?
        </p>
        <textarea id="q5" placeholder="If I only had to answer to myself..." rows="5"></textarea>
        <div class="step-nav">
          <button class="btn-secondary step-prev"><span class="arrow">←</span> back</button>
          <button class="btn-primary step-next">next <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 6 -->
    <div class="step" data-step="6">
      <div class="step-header">
        <span class="step-number">6 de 6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="ai-insight">
          <span class="ai-insight-marker">✦ reflection</span>
          <p class="ai-insight-text"></p>
        </div>
        <div class="step-encouragement"></div>
        <h2>One step in the right direction</h2>
        <p class="step-guide">
          You don't need to solve everything now. But you can take one small step in the direction
          the body pointed to. What would that step be? It could be a conversation, a pause,
          a "no", or simply paying more attention.
        </p>
        <textarea id="q6" placeholder="One step I can take is..." rows="5"></textarea>
        <div class="step-nav">
          <button class="btn-secondary step-prev"><span class="arrow">←</span> back</button>
          <button class="btn-primary" id="finish-btn">see my compass <span class="arrow">→</span></button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Result -->
    <div class="step" data-step="result">
      <div class="step-content result-content">
        <h2>Your compass</h2>
        <p class="result-intro">What surfaced when you stopped thinking and started feeling.</p>

        <div class="result-block"><h3>What unsettles me</h3><p id="r1"></p></div>
        <div class="result-block"><h3>What the head says</h3><p id="r2"></p></div>
        <div class="result-block"><h3>What the body says</h3><p id="r3"></p></div>
        <div class="result-block"><h3>Fear or misalignment</h3><p id="r4"></p></div>
        <div class="result-block"><h3>What my essential self wants</h3><p id="r5"></p></div>
        <div class="result-block closing-block"><h3>My next step</h3><p id="r6"></p></div>

        <div class="reflection-prompt">
          <span class="reflection-label">a question to take with you</span>
          <p class="reflection-text">When head and body disagree, which do you usually obey - and what changes if you switch?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reflection-counter"></div>

        <div class="result-actions">
          <button class="btn-secondary" id="copy-btn">copy text</button>
          <button class="btn-secondary" id="download-btn">save as text</button>
          <button class="btn-secondary" id="save-journal-btn">save to journal</button>
          <button class="btn-secondary" id="restart-btn">redo ↺</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<script>
  import { GuidedTool } from '../../scripts/guided-tool';
  import { initToolVisuals } from '../../scripts/tool-visuals';

  if (!(window as any).__guidedToolInit) {
    (window as any).__guidedToolInit = true;

  const config = {
    slug: 'bussola-interna',
    totalSteps: 6,
    fields: [
      { input: 'q1', output: 'r1' },
      { input: 'q2', output: 'r2' },
      { input: 'q3', output: 'r3' },
      { input: 'q4', output: 'r4' },
      { input: 'q5', output: 'r5' },
      { input: 'q6', output: 'r6' },
    ],
    encouragements: [
      '',
      'Naming the unease is already half the path.',
      'The head has its arguments. Now let\'s hear the other side.',
      'The body doesn\'t lie. Trust what it says.',
      'Knowing how to separate fear from misalignment is a superpower.',
      'Your essential self knows. Sometimes you just need to stop drowning it out.',
      'A small step in the right direction is worth more than a perfect plan.',
    ],
    closingReflection: 'When head and body disagree, which do you usually obey - and what changes if you switch?',
    resultTitle: 'Inner Compass',
    visualConfig: {
      type: 'compass-voices',
      sections: [
        { id: 'inquietacao', label: 'unease', stepRange: [1], wordClass: 'neutral' },
        { id: 'cabeca', label: 'head says', stepRange: [2], wordClass: 'fear' },
        { id: 'corpo', label: 'body says', stepRange: [3], wordClass: 'genuine' },
        { id: 'diagnostico', label: 'diagnosis', stepRange: [4], wordClass: 'strategy' },
        { id: 'eu-essencial', label: 'essential self', stepRange: [5], wordClass: 'genuine' },
        { id: 'proximo-passo', label: 'next step', stepRange: [6], wordClass: 'genuine' },
      ],
    },
  };

  const tool = new GuidedTool(config);
  tool.init();
  GuidedTool.wireExport(config);
  initToolVisuals(config.slug);

  }
</script>
